eNCA's Lindsay Dentlinger has more. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - It will cost at least R200-million to fix health facilities damaged by the KwaZulu-Natal floods. This was revealed in Parliament on Friday, as the health department briefed Members of Parliaments, on their spending plans for the coming year. READ: SANRAL suspends KZN toll fees The repair bill is more than three times the department’s total annual budget of R64-billion. eNCA's Lindsay Dentlinger has more in the video above.